<p>These compressed logs can be saved into a temporary file. These can then be edited as required and appended to current policy using the <code>ccs-loadpolicy</code> command:</p>

<pre class="command">
# cat /var/log/tomoyo/reject_002.log | /usr/sbin/ccs-sortpolicy &gt; ~/rejected.log
# vim ~/rejected.log
# /usr/sbin/ccs-loadpolicy -d &lt; ~/rejected.log
</pre>

<p>Since you are editing policy currently loaded into the kernel, changes will be lost if you shutdown the system without saving. Save "exception_policy.conf", "domain_policy.conf", "profile.conf" and "manager.conf" using this command:</p>

<pre class="command">
# /usr/sbin/ccs-savepolicy
</pre>

